\par 
\par }{\b\insrsid6771226 Option 2: Style Based Combat Skills
\par }{\insrsid6771226 This list is based off fighting styles, with the reasoning that a sword and shield fighter is not much different from a mace and shield fighter, practically speaking.
\par Archery - Bows and crossbows
\par Fencing - Fighting with light blades, knives, possibly cloaks and canes
\par Haft Weapon - Any weapon with a long haft, such as a spear, staff or polearm.
\par Improvisational - Fighting with whatever happens to be on hand.
\par Mounted - Fighting from horseback.
\par Single Weapon - Fighting with a weapon in one hand and nothing in particular in the other.
\par Thrown - Throwing things.
\par Two Handed - Non-hafted weapons large and heavy enough to require two hands.
\par Two Weapon - A Weapon in each hand. Other than looking cool, the main advantage of this style is the difficulty in disarming it.
\par Unarmed - Fighting unarmed, be it bare knuckle brawling or some manner of martial art.
\par Weapon and Shield - A one handed weapon in one hand, a shield in the other.
\par 
\par As an example, under this model, a character with archery at Good would be Good with any bow or crossbow he picked up.
\par 
\par }{\b\insrsid6771226 Option 3: Thematic Combat Skills
\par }{\insrsid6771226 This list is divided along more stylistic lines, with each skill representing a group of weapons of combat styles joined by their thematic elements rather than any real tactical similarity.
\par Archer - Bows and daggers
\par Brawler - Improvised weapons and unarmed attacks.
\par Cavalry - Mounted use of swords and bows.
\par Cutthroat - Knives, saps, garrotes.
\par }{\insrsid5639858 Duelist}{\insrsid6771226  - Use of fencing weapons
\par Footman - Use of swords, shields and polearms
\par Knight - Mounted lances and swords, as well as swords afoot.
\par Martial Artist - Unarmed attacks and weapons like staves or oddly curved blades.
\par Pirate - Cutlasses and belaying pins.
\par Ranger - Bows and swords.
\par There are many more possibilities for skills, but they should be tied to the world in some fashion - for example one school of }{\insrsid5639858 duelists}{\insrsid6771226  may have a different skillset than another.
